node.title: Body of missing man Travis Davis pulled from Sunshine Coast surf
node.alt: A photo of Travis Davis wearing a red hoodie.
node.description: The body of missing man Travis Davis is pulled from surf on Queensland's Sunshine Coast.
node.content:
["The body of missing man\u00a0Travis Davis\u00a0has been found\u00a0in waters off Shelly Beach near Caloundra,\u00a0almost 24 hours\u00a0after\u00a0he vanished along a treacherous stretch of shore.", "Water Police on jet skis found the man in waters south of where he went missing, Queensland police said in a statement.", "", "
The Westpac Rescue helicopter has been providing help since the morning.(ABC News)
", "Surf lifesaving crews have been at the scene\u00a0since before dawn, dispatching two rescue vessels\u00a0and\u00a0a surveillance drone in the hopes of finding the 20-year-old from Ferny Hills.", "The Westpac Rescue helicopter provided aerial support through the morning.", "Travis Davis and a second person were swimming at Shelly Beach in the late afternoon on Saturday when passers-by on the beach saw them begin to struggle.", "Three people entered the water to help the pair, but only one of the swimmers was pulled to safety.", "The second man, also in his 20s, remains in hospital.", "More to come."]
